radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated to 15mm with a large amount of fat stranding and small free fluid in the right paracolic gutter. An 8-mm hyperdensity at the appendiceal orifice is an appendicolith. Mildly distended fluid filled loops of small bowel may be a reactive ileus. The visualized lung bases are clear aside from mild dependent bibasilar atelectasis. No pleural or pericardial effusion, no renal stone, hydronephrosis or contour-altering renal mass. The liver, gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, and bilateral adrenal glands are normal. No drainable fluid collection or free air. Mild atherosclerotic calcifications noted throughout the normal caliber aorta.
